IQA Atomic Contributions to Diatomic "Interaction" Energy Components:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
  E_IQA_Inter(A,B)/2 = Vne(A,B)/2 + Ven(A,B)/2 + Vee(A,B)/2 + Vnn(A,B)/2
                     = Contribution to E_IQA(A) From "Interaction" of Atom A With Atom B
                     = Half of Total IQA "Interaction" Energy Between Atoms A and B
  Vne(A,B)/2 = Half of Attraction Energy Between Nucleus of Atom A and Electron Density Distribution of Atom B
  Ven(A,B)/2 = Half of Attraction Energy Between Electron Density Distribution of Atom A and Nucleus of Atom B
  Vee(A,B)/2 = Half of Two-electron Interaction Energy Between Atom A and Atom B
  Vnn(A,B)/2 = Half of Repulsion Energy Between Nucleus of Atom A and Nucleus of Atom B
  VeeC(A,B)/2 = Coulomb Part of Vee(A,B)/2
  VeeX(A,B)/2 = Exchange-Correlation Part of Vee(A,B)/2
  Note that:
       E_IQA_Inter(B,A)/2 = E_IQA_Inter(A,B)/2
       Vne(B,A)/2 = Ven(A,B)/2
       Ven(B,A)/2 = Vne(A,B)/2
       Vee(B,A)/2 = Vee(A,B)/2
       Vnn(B,A)/2 = Vnn(A,B)/2
       VeeC(B,A)/2 = VeeC(A,B)/2
       VeeX(B,A)/2 = VeeX(A,B)/2
  Note that, within numerical integration errors, we should have:
       E_IQA_Inter(A,SumB)/2 = E_IQA(A) - E_IQA_Intra(A)
       Vne(A,SumB)/2 = Vne(A,Mol)/2 - Vne(A,A)/2
       Ven(A,SumB)/2 = Ven(A,Mol)/2 - Ven(A,A)/2
       Vee(A,SumB)/2 = Vee(A,A')/2 = Vee(A) - Vee(A,A)
       VeeC(A,SumB)/2 = VeeC(A,A')/2 = VeeC(A) - VeeC(A,A)
       VeeX(A,SumB)/2 = VeeX(A,A')/2 = VeeX(A) - VeeX(A,A)
See "2EDM Note" and "DFT Note".
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
